This paper is primarily focused on ethical and explainable artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves machine learning-based autonomous agents, which is a subfield of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the social implications of autonomous systems, which could be categorized under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper introduces a novel formalism to describe the intrinsic knowledge and solutions of a VDA, which could be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
